Interview Optimization

Most accepted solutions use:

grid[r][c] = '0';

because:

visited array = extra memory

and the problem allows modifying the grid.


Full DFS Pattern

void dfs(int r, int c) {

    if(r < 0 || c < 0 ||
       r >= rows || c >= cols)
        return;

    if(grid[r][c] == '0')
        return;

    grid[r][c] = '0';

    dfs(r + 1, c);
    dfs(r - 1, c);
    dfs(r, c + 1);
    dfs(r, c - 1);
}



Main Logic
int islands = 0;

for(int r = 0; r < rows; r++) {

    for(int c = 0; c < cols; c++) {

        if(grid[r][c] == '1') {

            islands++;

            dfs(r, c);
        }
    }
}

